         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25/6/95. ¶  ¶ The byefollowing seeds (fruits) of Verticordia grandis, dear Dr Dyer, have just freshly arrived from the Murchison-River. ¶  I would advise that the  ¶ capsules ¶   ¶ be ¶   ¶ cautiously...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.06.25a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1891-6, f. 78.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25/6/95.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Date stamped</seg>: Royal Gardens Kew 30.JUL. 95.; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">annotated in black ink by W. Watson</seg>: 348/1895 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">i.e. register number in Kew </seg>Inwards Book <seg style="font-style: italic; ">of specimens received</seg>), <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and in red ink by W. Hemsley</seg>: Ansd. 3.8.95<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>(<seg style="font-style: italic; ">letter not found</seg>).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The byefollowing seeds (fruits) of <name key="Verticordia%20grandis">Verticordia grandis</name>, dear Dr Dyer, have just freshly arrived from the Murchison-River.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>WA.</p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note> I would advise that the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">capsules</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">be</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">cautiously</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">opened</hi>
               </seg> and the one or more <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">perfect seeds be taken out</hi>
               </seg> and sown <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">unencumbered</hi>
               </seg> by the floral envelopes and be sown in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sandy-moory soil</hi>
               </seg> and also sandy-clayey and experimentally also in other mixtures of soil. Naturally this V. and V. oculata grow on sand plains, but their area is very limited and nowhere are they gregarious. If the seeds are liberated for sowing, the seedlings will have the best chance at their earliest state to fix themselves to the soil. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope soon to get the fruits also of the indescribably beautiful V. oculata. If you have them once, doubtless these two magnificent V. could be multiplied from cuttings (of not too old wood) with bottom-warmth under a bell-glass</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Encourage me kindly in letting me know whether you had any success in this promising culture.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Verticordia%20grandis">Verticordia grandis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Verticordia%20oculata">Verticordia oculata</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
